"title": "8827: selfishness",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8827",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A self-centred concern for oneself, without due regard to the needs of others. Scripture treats selfishness as an aspect of sin and urges believers to care for others as well as themselves.</p>\n<h2>Selfishness is a characteristic of the sinner</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:5\">ROM 8:5</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:15\">2CO 5:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov18:1\">PRO 18:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:8\">ROM 2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:3\">EPH 2:3</a></p>\n<h2>Selfishness is a characteristic of sinful society</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:1-2Tim3:2\">2TI 3:1–3:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg17:6\">JDG 17:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg21:25\">JDG 21:25</a></p>\n<h2>Expressions of selfishness</h2>\n<h3>Greed</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:25\">MAT 23:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:7\">MRK 12:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:13-Luke12:21\">LUK 12:13–12:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:3\">ACT 5:3</a></p>\n<h3>Ambition</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:3\">PHP 2:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer45:5\">JER 45:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:19-Gal5:20\">GAL 5:19–5:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:17\">PHP 1:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:14-Jas3:16\">JAS 3:14–3:16</a></p>\n<h3>Boastfulness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:30\">DAN 4:30</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Examples of selfishness</h2>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen11:4\">GEN 11:4</a> <em>the builders of the tower of Babel</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen13:10-Gen13:11\">GEN 13:10–13:11</a> <em>Lot in his choice of territory</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek28:2-Ezek28:5\">EZK 28:2–28:5</a> <em>the king of Tyre</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:8\">EZK 34:8</a> <em>Israel's leaders</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:35\">MRK 10:35</a> <em>James and John</em></p>\n<h2>Self-absorption as the result of pain or depression</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job14:22\">JOB 14:22</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:10\">1KI 19:10</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Antidotes to selfishness</h2>\n<h3>God's word</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:36\">PSA 119:36</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The example of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:3\">ROM 15:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:4-Phil2:8\">PHP 2:4–2:8</a></p>\n<h3>Dying to the old nature</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:6\">ROM 6:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:22\">EPH 4:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:9\">COL 3:9</a></p>\n<h3>Serving one another</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:10\">1PE 4:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:24\">1CO 10:24</a></p>\n<h3>Loving one another</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:34\">JHN 13:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:39\">MAT 22:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:8-Rom13:10\">ROM 13:8–13:10</a></p>",
